Now we build STEP 9 — Gallery Page 📸
This page is very important for a goshala because donors want to see real photos of cows, shelter, and activities. It builds trust.

We’ll use a simple image gallery powered by your public/images folder.


---

STEP 9.1 — Upload gallery images

Put images inside:

public/images/gallery/

If folder doesn’t exist, create it.

Example:

public/images/gallery/cow1.jpg
public/images/gallery/cow2.jpg
public/images/gallery/shelter.jpg
public/images/gallery/feeding.jpg


---

STEP 9.2 — Create gallery page

📁 File

src/pages/gallery.astro

Paste this code:

---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const images = [

"/images/gallery/cow1.jpg",
"/images/gallery/cow2.jpg",
"/images/gallery/shelter.jpg",
"/images/gallery/feeding.jpg",

];
---

<MainLayout title="Gallery">

<section class="section">

<div class="container">

<h1 class="section-title">
Goshala Gallery
</h1>

<p style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:40px;">
See our cows, shelter, and daily seva activities.
</p>


<div class="grid">

{
images.map(image => (

<div class="card">

<img src={image} alt="Goshala image">

</div>

))
}

</div>


</div>

</section>

</MainLayout>


---

